+# Repository Guidelines
+
+## Project Structure & Module Organization
+
+This is a Java 25 Spring Boot service that synchronizes files from GCS to POS controllers through the TCx Sky file API. Source code lives under `src/main/java/com/elrosado/synchrosrv` and follows a hexagonal layout: `domain` contains records, exceptions, and ports; `application` contains orchestration services; `infrastructure` contains Pub/Sub handlers, GCS, SQL Server, Secret Manager, and TCx Sky adapters. Tests mirror this structure in `src/test/java`. Runtime configuration is in `src/main/resources/application*.yaml`; Kubernetes and container assets are in `k8s/`, `Dockerfile`, `docker/dev/Dockerfile`, `build.sh`, and `skaffold.yaml`.
+
+## Build, Test, and Development Commands
+
+- `.\mvnw.cmd clean package` builds the service and runs tests on Windows.
+- `./mvnw clean package` is the equivalent for Unix-like shells.
+- `.\mvnw.cmd test` runs unit tests and generates the JaCoCo report.
+- `.\mvnw.cmd spring-boot:run "-Dspring-boot.run.profiles=local"` starts the app locally.
+- `bash build.sh` builds and pushes Podman images to `localhost:30500`.
+
+Use the Maven wrapper whenever possible.
+
+## Coding Style & Naming Conventions
+
+Use 4-space Java indentation and keep package boundaries explicit. Input ports belong in `domain.port.in`, output ports in `domain.port.out`, application orchestration in `application.service`, and adapters in `infrastructure.adapter`. Use generic transfer names in this service, such as `TransferFileService`, `TransferEvent`, and `SynchroControllerSubscriber`. Test classes should use the class name plus `Test`.
+
+## Testing Guidelines
+
+The project uses `spring-boot-starter-test`, Mockito, AssertJ, and JaCoCo. Add focused tests for handlers, services, adapters, and configuration properties. Mock external systems such as Pub/Sub, GCS, Secret Manager, SQL Server, and TCx Sky. Run `.\mvnw.cmd test` before opening a pull request.
+
+## Commit & Pull Request Guidelines
+
+Recent commits use short summaries, including `feature: ...` and Spanish descriptions. Prefer concise imperative messages with optional prefixes like `feature:`, `fix:`, or `test:`. Pull requests should describe the behavior changed, list configuration or deployment impacts, include test evidence, and link related work items when available.
+
+## Event Integration
+
+Producers must publish generic transfer events to `retail.local.synchro.controller.v1`. Required fields are `codStore`, `gcsBucket`, `gcsPath`, `fileName`, and `targetDir`. See `INTEGRACION_SYNCHRO_CONTROLLER.md` for the contract and examples.
+
+## Security & Configuration Tips
+
+Do not commit real credentials, bearer tokens, database passwords, or production secret values. `targetDir` and GCS location are event data, not static service properties.


